            <h1>7. Cultural & Spiritual Evolution</h1>
        </header>

        <section class="category-article" style="margin-bottom: 40px; font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.8;">
            <p>Cultural perceptions of dreams have shifted from divine revelations to secular self-analysis. Ancient Egyptians built "Dream Temples" for healing, while indigenous cultures use "Vision Quests" for social guidance. In the modern era, dreams are often viewed as a form of personal self-actualization. This dimension explores how our cultural lens dictates our relationship with the subconscious, reflecting the broader evolution of human belief systems and meaning-making.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="category-wp-content">
<figure class="wp-block-uagb-image__figure"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="/media-images/posts/history-of-dream-interpretation-illustration-1.webp" alt="Illustration for 7. Cultural & Spiritual Evolution" class="uag-image-1584" width="1200" height="550" title="7. Cultural & Spiritual Evolution" role="img"></figure>
</section>



